-- Japanese Bought Net 869.7 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   D a n i e l   P e t r i e
-- 2012-06-27T23:57:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/japanese-bought-net-869-7-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 22 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 869.7 billion yen ($10.9 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 18.2 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 8.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 896 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 313.9 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 50.4 billion yen in stocks, and bought 424 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 160.4
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
